<br>
There are just some zones\camps that yield quite a bit better quantity\quality of loot. <br>
<br>
The cost of spells helps increase wealth for those winning rolls on runes and specs. <br>
<br>
Some zones are known for being good &quot;gem dropping&quot; zones. Not just for AE groups either. A two man operation at NG in seb during an afternoon can net out about 2k per man in gems if you get a little luck on some of the better gems. And that would be just one after noon(2 to 3 hours). <br>
<br>
WW is good for tradeskill components, SG for quest gems. PoP zones have some stuff that sells decent to vendors, ie 15pp per to 80 or more pp per. <br>
<br>
For me the common denomenator in producing wealth was having a high level character of a class thatis in demand in group or teams that venture to such places for exp\loot. <br>
<br>
Also be aware that some of the more wealthy people in EQ are switching out nice droppable loot for nodrop stuff they get as the result of raiding alot. So another possible common denomenator is rich EQ people play alot.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kahel>kahel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/03 4:03:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4063.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where is the money coming from?</span><hr size=1> It all about finding new stuff first and going place that are usually abandonned.<br>
<br>
Pre-PoP i would 2 box my bard and my friend cleric and go donw the well in Siren Grotto .  Once down the well the sirens were a joke to kill but they dropped alot of BP gems (Flawless diamonds , Black Marble and Pristine Emeralds) usually the BP gems were hard to find cause no one went there .   In like 4 hours i could get like 6-7 Flawless diamond that i sold 4kpp , 7-8 Black marble wich i sold 2kpp and 8-9 pristine emeralds wich were sellable for 1-2kpp .  <br>
<br>
That like 40kpp for 4 hours .    of course once other people learn about something the market get flooded and your value goes down.  <br>
<br>
When PoP came out people had limited access to spectral so spectral spells went for like 50kpp + per spells , it was easy for someone who could solo HoH to get some spectrals to sell .<br>
<br>
Farming Cazic once it got revamped is also a good way to make cash , Boot of the flowing slime were 100k pp+ at the start and the common drop .  someone with the ressource to farm that could make 500kpp+ easily in a week or 2 .<br>
<br>
<br>
The influx of PP itself was mostly due to macros and tradeskill bugs , were someone could program his EQ to make tradeskill stuff and sell it for a small profit but when you leave that running over night you can get alot of PP in the end wich flooded the market with more PP.<br>
