<br>
The rest is just a matter of redistributing the total mass of PP between players, and the Bazaar and channels made EQ much more liquid in terms of selling items, easier access for buyer to meet seller.<br>
<br>
Maybe some item priced high at a bazaar seller would work as an incentive for farming plat that you wouldn't normally do and then inflate the economy. <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370955 target=blank>Sage Aauminki Iceblade</a><br><a href=http://www.vazaelle.dk target=blank>Caer Cadarn</a></big><br>Vazaelle Server</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qxired>Q Xired</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1829<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/03 6:39:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4063.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://quarken2012.homestead.com/files/face1.jpg border= 0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where is the money coming from?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It all about finding new stuff first<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
