<br>
From what I can tell these are the keys to be rich in EQ. Mind you the most I have ever had liquid at one time is 140k, it may seem like a fortune to many, at the same time I am sure its paltry to many others.<br>
<br>
Access- A level 65 has more access than a 60 same thing applies to a level 55. I spend most of my time now playing my level 52 warrior but he sure as hell doesn't pay the bills. Levels go a long way in getting you to the cash camps and rare drops.<br>
<br>
Patience- Now more than ever great gear is available to everyone, /wave bazaar. It comes down to the time a person is willing to wait to get that good deal or have the item they want to buy come up for sale. It also comes down to the way you buy your upgrades. If you are constantly upgrading a little bit at a time, to get you thru the next couple of levels. I have found this is a great way to lose money. My warrior at level 9 was wearing a fungi, but he didn’t have any shoes. I have found it is best to just buy gear that will last you a lot of levels. I know the tradesman will hate me for this, but never buy &quot;new&quot; trades items, no matter how good they look. Just taking the Ring of Gallantry (not the real name I know but it escapes me). Great item, for me it covers the spectrum of what I consider a good piece of gear should have, AC,Stats,Resists Direct hitpts/mana. Look at the way the price has dropped in the last 3 months. Look for gear that drops from set timer mobs. I have found that those keep their value the best. HOH has been around for a long time, but keeps its value rather well considering the mob that drops it is on a set respawn.<br>
<br>
Luck- Pretty much speaks for itself. You could be a druid that never had more than 15k in his life, get invited to a pick up CT sewers group and a hour later have in your possession Boots of Flowing Slime. Sometimes it really does come down to fortunes being made on the roll of a dice. Also, Luck and Access are in bed together a lot.<br>
<br>
Discipline- Holding to your prices in the bazaar. Not taking the small upgrades when a few more K will get you what you really want, etc. This is probly the hardest of the 4 to achieve.<br>
<br>
Then there are always the seedier ways to earn a dollar. You have a 55 cleric, Pling is an option for you. Its good cash, you'll feel like a whore doing it, but take a shower and head to the bazaar with a full pocket, chances are you will feel better.<br>
<br>
Ebaying is a way. I have no exp. with this but I think it would take more than a shower to feel better.<br>
<br>
Of course this is just my advice, take it for what you feel its worth. It is given free and that’s kinda hard to beat.<br>
<br>
Ashture 61/108 Druid Of CN<br>
